{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3496341,"name":"","username":"jacob_mazelin","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jacob_mazelin/{size}/213574_2.png","created_at":"2025-01-30T03:20:58.351Z","cooked":"<p>Hello! We are trying to use Pathplanner’s PathfindtoPose command, but we’re running into multiple problems. I know there is a solution for each problem, but I’m having a hard time figuring out what they are. The lineup code works perfectly in simulation (without the Apriltags), so I’m thinking it has something to do with our AprilTags and Limelight. We’re using a Kracken drivetrain and the new Limelight 4 with MegaTag2.</p>
<p>Problem <span class="hashtag-raw">#1:</span> When I hit the path button, the robot drives to the default position in our switch case instead of to the tag it currently sees. We have our switch case connected to the TID value from the limelight, so for example, if it sees tag 7, it will drive to the left or right side of AprilTag 7 depending on if you hit the left or right trigger. This means our switch case isn’t updating with the correct tag.<br>
Problem <span class="hashtag-raw">#2:</span> When we tested the lineup with the default tag in our switch case, the robot would drive away from the tag instead of towards it , or it would try to turn 180 degrees then stop when it lost sight of the tag. It is possible that our rotation2d is 180 degrees off, but our poses are definitely correct. My initial guess is that something is wrong with the Limelight Field-Space Localization or Pathplanner’s Autobuilder.</p>
<p>I did attempt to bypass the switch case by making a pathfind command in RobotContainer, but that ran into the same issues. Our switch case, limelight, and Pathplanner AutoBuilder are located in CommandSwerveDrivetrain.java, and the button command is in RobotContainer. I would greatly appreciate someone more experienced than me to look at our code and see if you can find any issues with our switch case or Pathplanner/Limelight configuration. Here is our code: <a href="https://github.com/team5675/2025Robot" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://github.com/team5675/2025Robot</a>. Thank you for your help!</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-30T03:20:58.351Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":345,"reads":292,"readers_count":291,"score":1778.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":484242,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/team5675/2025Robot","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - team5675/2025Robot: Team 5675's Official 2025 Comp Bot Repo","clicks":31}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57331,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5675 Team Captain"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem/484242/1","custom_user_title":"5675 Team Captain","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"top