<p>In your driveToPose command, there aren’t any protections to make sure an aprilTag is being seen before being ran. When you press right trigger, if your limelight can’t see a tag, the command should be printing “Warning: No valid AprilTag detected. Defaulting to A_BLUE.”.</p>
<p>Take a look at limelighthelpers ‘hasTarget’ boolean and find some ways to only run your driveToPose command when you can see a tag (or at least you remember the last tag you’ve seen <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/wink.png?v=12" title=":wink:" class="emoji" alt=":wink:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20">).</p>
<p>Cool solution for reef alignment, happy troubleshooting <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/grin.png?v=12" title=":grin:" class="emoji" alt=":grin:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-30T20:39:13.144Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":12,"reads":173,"readers_count":172,"score":99.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":484242,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem","display_username":"James Barnes","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":57331,"username":"jacob_mazelin","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jacob_mazelin/{size}/213574_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":71854,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem/484242/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3497175,"name":"","username":"jacob_mazelin","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jacob_mazelin/{size}/213574_2.png","created_at":"2025-01-30T22:34:43.880Z","cooked":"<p>My mistake, I thought the -19 was for the limelight pitch, but it’s actually the robot pitch which should definitely be zero. I did use Pathplanner’s telemetry window, and the button activated the path, but the robot either turned 180 degrees then stopped when it lost sight of the tag or it tried to move but was unsuccessful. The path runs perfectly in simulation, however, and here is a video showing it: <a href="https://youtu.be/ZjrR40I3IdY" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://youtu.be/ZjrR40I3IdY</a>.</p>
<p>When I was troubleshooting, one of the problems I fixed was Pathplanner starting the path from (0,0) instead of the robot pose, and I fixed that by putting <code>this.m_poseEstimator.getEstimatedPosition()</code> in the AutoBuilder. Before, it was getState().Pose, which was always returning (0,0) instead of the current pose. Could that be the same for getState().Speeds? Could that be an issue if Speeds also returns zero? Thanks for the tip!</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-30T22:34:43.880Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":156,"readers_count":155,"score":41.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":484242,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://youtu.be/ZjrR40I3IdY","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":10}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":71854,"username":"NotJames","name":"James Barnes","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/notjames/{size}/246860_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57331,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5675 Team Captain"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem/484242/4","custom_user_title":"5675 Team Captain","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3497242,"name":"James Barnes","username":"NotJames","avatar_template":