<p>Setting cameraPose to a -18 degree shift I think needs to be in Radians, not degrees.</p>
<p>Use the units class</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-02-02T14:59:08.383Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":125,"readers_count":124,"score":30.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":484242,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem","display_username":"James Barnes","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":57331,"username":"jacob_mazelin","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jacob_mazelin/{size}/213574_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":71854,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pathfind-to-pose-problem/484242/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3499887,"name":"James Barnes","username":"NotJames","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/notjames/{size}/246860_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-02T15:56:36.584Z","cooked":"<p>Double checked, I’m wrong, degrees is correct.</p>
<p>I do think the issue is specifically coming from seeding the limelight to the robot.  I see in your code that ‘limelightHelpers.setRobotOrientation’ is called quite a lot.</p>
<p>What’s catching my eye is that you set the camera position differently depending on if you’re red alliance or blue alliance (line 339)</p>
